Booting to the command line
<p>
To disable Kodi from starting at boot run the following command and launch a shell on the screen at bootup, run the following commands:
<pre>sudo systemctl disable mediacenter</pre>
<pre>sudo systemctl enable getty@tty1</pre>
</p>
<p>
After a reboot, these changes will be active.
</p>
<h2>Reverting these changes</h2>
<p>
To revert these changes, run the following commands:
<pre>sudo systemctl enable mediacenter</pre>
<pre>sudo systemctl disable getty@tty1</pre>
</p>
After a reboot, these changes will be active.
